<br>
The absolute first things to focus on are haste, AC and hitpoints. Haste will make a huge difference in your damage output, but can be awfully expensive. AC and HP can be worked on relatively cheaply.<br>
<br>
Wisdom: At your level, wisdom won't do much for you but mana items will. Don't sacrafice tanking abilities, though, as your spells aren't worth casting (for the most part). Much later on, you'll want to start adding more wisdom.<br>
<br>
Agility: get it over 75 and then don't worry about. It's certainly nice when there's an item with high AC AND agility, but don't sacrafice AC, HP, etc. for it.<br>
<br>
Dexterity: Ignore it. Have to add huge amounts to see a difference in proc rates. Doesn't do anything else for you (slightly increases how quickly you learn some skills). <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231378">Romidar Trueblade</a>
